    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Project Report on Low Cost Wireless Control and Monitoring of Batch Process Using Plc and Dcs</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Anand, Abhishek<br />Bhardwaj, Abhishek<br />Sahoo, Abhishek</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Low Cost Wireless Control<br />Plc and Dcs</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6110</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Due to increasing cost pressures, it is becoming more and more difficult to justify specialized activities such as the operation of a diagnostics station or the exclusive use of specialists at a single plant. In contrast, in a centralized remote monitoring facility with PLC and DCS, specialists can be employed to provide support to a far greater number of plants simultaneously. The functionality of the PLC has evolved over the years through wired communication.
The advantage of wireless communication over wired communication lies in its mobility, neat and easy installation, less cost of cabling infrastructure and more user support. But using a PLC wireless module or a wireless modem for wireless exchange of information gets very expensive.
Hence ZigBee Module can be used along with PLC to transmit data to and back from the process. ZigBee wireless network can operate in a wide range of environments and provide advantages in cost, size, power, flexibility and distributed intelligence compared to wired technologies.
The process to be controlled using a PLC and DCS is a Batch Process measuring and maintaining temperature, level and flow. PLC may include logic for single-variable feedback analog/digital control loop like ON - OFF control for e.g. a ON-OFF feedback loop could be used to control the temperature, level and flow process is visualized, monitored and remotely controlled by PLC and DCS</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17426">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17426</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17097">ICE-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
